{# Periodic reflection — compress older raw memories into a gist paragraph.
   Models the gist-vs-verbatim psychological distinction
   (Reyna-Brainerd fuzzy-trace; Murre-Dros 2015 forgetting curve).

   The reflection now ALSO probes for political shift: did the events of this
   period change my views vs. where I started? This is the explicit handle
   that lets belief drift accumulate instead of every memory item being a
   noisy paragraph the LLM has to re-derive a vote from. #}

You are looking back at memories from {{ period_start }} to {{ period_end }}. Below are specific events you reacted to during that period:

{% for m in memories -%}
[{{ m.timestamp }}] {{ m.content }}

{% endfor %}

Two questions:

1. **Gist**: forgetting the specific details and dates, write 2-3 first-person
   sentences capturing what STILL FEELS IMPORTANT to you about this period —
   what stuck, what you'd still mention if someone asked you about it now.

2. **Political shift**: how have your political views moved during this period
   compared to where you started? Did anything strengthen your support for a
   party? Did anything weaken it? Be specific — say "I'm now leaning more
   toward TMC because of X" or "BJP lost me when Y happened" or "still
   supporting the same party for the same reasons" if no shift.

Output ONLY a JSON object:

```json
{
  "content": "<2-3 first-person sentences capturing the gist of what stuck>",
  "importance": <integer 1-10, how much this period still matters>,
  "political_shift": "<one sentence: which party I lean toward now and why,
    explicitly compared to where I started this period>"
}
```
